e work, and reflect on how architecture can respond to today’s material and environmental urgencies, with clay at the centre.___Tickets are free with a donation to our local charity partners Made In Hackney.	Clay | Culture | Carbon: 'Meet The Makers'	Explore the innovative Clay | Culture | Carbon exhibition and engage directly with the visionary makers, collaborators, and curators behind it. This special Studio Late event takes place on 10 July 2024.	Explore the innovative Clay | Culture | Carbon exhibition and engage directly with the visionary makers, collaborators, and curators behind it.	Join us for a unique 'Meet The Makers' Studio Late event, offering an exclusive after-hours exploration of the 'Clay | Culture | Carbon' exhibition. This special evening is designed to connect you directly with the creative minds, dedicated collaborators, and insightful curators who brought this compelling show to life. Discover how the exhibition delves into clay as a multifaceted medium, exploring its role in carbon sequestration, its cultural significance, and the power of collaborative making.\n\nGain direct insights into the exhibition’s craft-focused, research-led, and community-rooted methodologies through engaging conversations. You'll hear from exhibition curator Elly Ward Morris, and learn about 'co-making' principles with David Storring, Head of Sustainability, and Edie Parfitt from CELLA, the collective behind the central installation. The event will also feature discussions on low-carbon alternatives to traditional fired bricks, including Earth bricks from Arup's Materials Team and 'Circulabrick' by Lyons & Annoot. Furthermore, discover the fascinating work of 'Hackney Potter' Adele Williams, who masterfully transforms foraged raw clay into experimental pieces.\n\nThis event offers a valuable opportunity to understand how architecture can effectively respond to pressing material and environmental challenges by embracing sustainable practices with clay. It's especial